{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889625247,"sessionID":"ses_284bc2356ffen9PxcrKpTk3VSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7b453072001YsTLOMvybmgMM6","messageID":"msg_d7b4529e9001lehQUJ9bSfRbY1","sessionID":"ses_284bc2356ffen9PxcrKpTk3VSR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e5227c9b58094b68a0a1785e7ca60929","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Dify plugin — file map\n6: \n7: | File | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n10: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n11: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n12: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n13: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n14: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n15: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n16: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n17: \n18: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n19: \n20: From source:\n21: \n22: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n23: - `type`: `plugin`\n24: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n25: - `name`: `agentcube`\n26: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n27: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n28: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n29: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n30: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n31: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n32: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n33: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n34: \n35: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n36: \n37: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n38: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n39: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n40: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n41: \n42: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n43: \n44: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n45: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n46: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n47: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n48: \n49: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n50: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n51: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n52: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n53: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n54: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n55: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n56: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n57: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n58: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n59: \n60: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n61: \n62: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n66: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n67: \n68: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n69:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n70:         try:\n71:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n72:         except Exception as e:\n73:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n74: ```\n75: \n76: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n77: \n78: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: from collections.abc import Generator\n82: from typing import Any\n83: from dify_plugin import Tool\n84: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n85: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n86: \n87: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n88:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n89:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n90:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n91: \n92:     def execute(\n93:         self,\n94:         router_url=None,\n95:         workload_manager_url=None,\n96:         language=\"python\",\n97:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n98:         session_id=None,\n99:         code=None,\n100:         command=None,\n101:         session_reuse=False,\n102:         **kwargs\n103:     ): ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n107: \n108: ```\n109: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n110: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n114: \n115: | File | Role |\n116: |------|------|\n117: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n118: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n119: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n120: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n121: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n122: \n123: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n124: \n125: ### Globals / config (selected)\n126: \n127: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n128: |------|--------|-----------------|\n129: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n130: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n131: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n132: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n133: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n134: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n135: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n136: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n137: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n138: \n139: ### Core classes / functions\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: class SandboxRunner:\n143:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n144:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n145:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n146:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     def stop(self): ...\n148: \n149: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n150: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n151: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n152: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n153: \n154: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n155: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n156: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n157: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n159: \n160: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n161:     script: str\n162:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n163:     report: str\n164: \n165: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### FastAPI endpoints\n169: \n170: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n171: |--------|------|----------------------|\n172: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n173: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n174: \n175: ### Imports of note\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n179: from pydantic import BaseModel\n180: import uvicorn\n181: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n182: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n183: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n184: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n185: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n189: \n190: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n191: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n192: - Container port `8000` TCP\n193: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n194: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n195: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n196: \n197: ## Dockerfile highlights\n198: \n199: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n200: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n201: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n202: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n203: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n204: \n205: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n206: \n207: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n208: \n209: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin — file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775889625226,"end":1775889625244}}}}
